    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(S.) In nomine sancte et individue Trinitatis. Anno dominice incarnationis
                        eiusdem millesimo centesimo XIIII, de mense iunii, indicione VII. Sancta
                        autem <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> de loco <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/2400">Insula iuxta Padi</placeName> in honore <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Churches #Landed_possessions #Mansi #Forests #Agricultural_workers #Specialized_workers"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti</orgName> consecrata cui
                            <persName key="#Monasteries #Abbots" ref="#people/2189"
                            >Albericus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> preesse videtur, ego quidem in Dei nomine <rs
                            key="#Countess #childOf #Salian #Public_rituals">comitissa</rs>
                        <persName
                            key="#Countess #childOf #Salian #Public_rituals #Landed_possessions #Mansi #Forests #Agricultural_workers #Specialized_workers"
                            ref="#people/125">Matilda</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchionis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke #parentOf" ref="#people/1">Bonifatii</persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filia</rs>, que professa sum lege <rs key="#Salian"
                            >Salica</rs> vivere, presentibus dixi: Quod ad meritum anime mee
                        pertinere potest, necesse est mihi semper illud agere unde in hoc et in
                        futuro seculo plenam apud omnipotentem Dominum maximam passim consequi
                        mercedem. Ideoque ego qui supra comitissa Matilda concedo et trado habere
                        suprascripte ecclesie <rs key="#Landed_possessions">omnes res</rs> illas
                        sicuti recte et laborate fuerunt ex mea parte in loco <placeName
                            key="#Mansi" ref="#places/2959">Casaleavoni</placeName> per <rs
                                key="#Agricultural_workers">massarium</rs> qui vocatur <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Gumbertus/de Casalevoni"/>Compertum</persName> de Casaleavoni,
                        et <rs key="#Mansi">mansum</rs> unum sicuti rectum fuit per <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Dominicus/Silvus"> Dominicum
                                Silvum</name></persName>, et alium mansum medium sicuti detemptum et
                        laboraturn fuit per <persName key="#Agricultural_workers">
                            <name ref="Rusticus/de Insula">Rusticum</name></persName> de Insula
                        ubicumque invente fuerint, et ronccuras de loco qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Forests">Dosso de Falcone</placeName> cum <rs
                            key="#Forests">busco</rs> ibi habente sicuti designatum fuit ad
                        suprascriptam ecclesiam ex parte domine comitisse Matildis; et <rs
                            key="#Specialized_workers">piscatorem</rs> unum in <placeName
                            key="#Natural_landscape"><rs key="#Natural_landscape">valle</rs>
                            Cultroni</placeName>; et ubicumque piscatores de Casaleavone piscant
                        concedimus eiusdem ecclesie, ut suprascriptam ecclesiam habeat et teneat
                        suprascriptas res, et faciant in usum et sumptum cunctorum monachorum qui in
                        eadem ecclesia militant et qui militaturi sunt quicquid voluerint sine omni
                        mea et heredum ac proheredurn meorum contradicione, pro mercede anime mee
                        atque patris seu matris mee. <rs key="#Public_rituals">Insuper per
                            cultellum, festucum nodatum, vuantonem et vuasonem terre atque ramum
                            arboris coram testibus legitimam facio vobis concessionem</rs> cum omni
                        honore sicuti mihi pertinere videntur, salva reverentia <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1100">romane ecclesie</orgName>. Si vero, quod
                        futurum esse non credo, si ego comitissa Matilda, quod absit aut ullus de
                        heredibus hac proheredibus meis seu ulla alia qualibet opposita persona
                        contra hanc <rs key="#Cartula">cartulam</rs> venire aut eam per quodvis
                        ingenium infringe[re] quesierimus, tunc inferamus parti contra quam exinde
                        litem intulerirnus mulctam que est <rs key="#Penalty">penam auri uncias
                            quattuor et argenti octo</rs>; et quod repetierimus vendicare non
                        valeamus, et comprehensum ab omni contradicente homine defendere; et si
                        defendere non potuerimus aut si vobis exinde aliquid per quodlibet ingenium
                        subtrahere quesierimus, tunc <rs key="#Penalty">in duplum</rs> suprascriptas
                        res ut supra legitur vobis restituere, sicut pro tempore valuerit in
                        consimilibus locis. Actum in <placeName key="#Mountains" ref="#places/2979"
                                ><rs key="#Mountains">monte</rs> Baronzioni</placeName> feliciter.
                        Matilda Dei gratia si quid est, + Huius cartulae fuerunt <rs key="#Witness"
                            >testes</rs>
                        <persName key="#Witness #Cartula" ref="#people/3525">Rainerius</persName> de
                        Saxo, <persName key="#Witness #Cartula" ref="#people/2193">Saxo</persName>
                        de Bibianello, <persName key="#Witness #Cartula"><name ref="Malabranca"
                                >Malabranca</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Cartula"
                                ><name ref="Gheradus/de Nogara">Girardus</name></persName> de
                            <placeName ref="#places/145">Nogara</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Cartula"><name ref="Martinus/Blanco">Martinus
                                Blanco</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Cartula"><name
                                ref="Bonussenior">Bonussenior</name></persName>, <persName
                                    key="#Witness #Cartula" ref="#people/4009">Marchise</persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Cartula"><name
                                ref="Bernardus/Balbus">Bernardus Balbus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Cartula"><name ref="Atto/de Salezola"
                            >Ato</name></persName> de <placeName>Salezola</placeName> et plures
                        alii. </ab>
                </div>
